I would like to merge this change by the end of 11/30/2015, unless there are additional comments.

The motivation for this change seems to be that when there is a key column lacking predicates, MDAM is not taking this into account. Please take a look at the fix to JIRA [TRAFODION-1641](here: https://github.com/apache/incubator-trafodion/pull/186) as I believe that addresses this problem.

Yes, we have two defenses to assure MDAM is suitable: the heuristics and
the cost.  Both are needed as both are not perfect due to various reasons.

This fix is to improve the heuristics part of the defense.

I didn't look at the details of how the TDB is implemented, but the overall idea of a "get region stats" looks good to me. Another way would have been to do this as a TMUDF, that would have avoided the "using" clause, but our current TMUDF interface may not have all the necessary interfaces. Once we support SQL in TMUDFs, we could put a simple TMUDF on top of this function.

Regarding .gitignore - I believe it is used to make sure that files untracked by Git remain untracked.

Following commands are executed after a build to check on tracked/untracked files:
   modified=$(git ls-files -m | wc -l)
   unignored=$(git ls-files -o --exclude-standard | wc -l)

In the regression test,  you have some calls to "hbase shell flush" . Looks like you're using swhbase . But that  may not work on clusters or official build machines. You may need to resplace those with "regrhbase" calls.
Merging since all comments have been addressed to reviewers satisfaction and tests pass.

The JSON output is primarily used by a python script parses the stdout and will try to parse as json. If the result is not a valid JSON, the python script will mark that as an error and continue to the next iteration.

A normal json response with values as 0 will be misleading. The python script tries to convert the values as numbers. So a null will not work in the python code.

So best to just return a error text that is not json. The script that uses the JSON response can handle the output.
